{
  "stem": "2581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I remember one time in particular, I was the dressed in a nice high school uniform.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I didn't go to high school, but my father was a tailor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So he dressed me a little bit in advance.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I carried the flag-- the Polish flag going to the synagogue on Polish Independence Day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we passed my grandfather's house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And on the way back, he called me in and gave me 20 grosze.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that was a lot of money.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I knew it was an expression of love, the only way my grandfather could.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He couldn't say, I love you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But that-- that was-- excuse me-- and I knew what he meant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He meant to say that I love you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I'm proud of you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on my father's side, I only had a grandmother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She wasn't, what we would say, comfortable.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was a woman that-- she was very old.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To me, that time, she looked very old, but she had to be anywhere between 70 and 80, or closer to 80.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And yet, she was sitting in the marketplace, as I will show you a picture that we have in [NON-ENGLISH] album, always murmuring or memorizing a prayer while she was selling her vegetables in the marketplace.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the synagogue, she was what is called in Yiddish, [YIDDISH], that she would read the prayers and other women that couldn't read the Hebrew would repeat after her.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the humorous side that the children always would watch her doing, is she would sit by her window Saturday afternoon and read her [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But actually what she did was watching if any Jewish person doesn't go in the movie house on Saturday afternoon.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
